Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.13,0:01:58.01,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,{\fad(770,770)\fnTimes New Roman\an3\fs18\blur2\bord1\shad0\3c&H4B4B4C&\pos(610.933,308.266)}Romeo and Juliet
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.79,0:02:00.67,Main,Shizuka,0,0,0,,An article about {\i1}Arabian Nights{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.67,0:02:02.17,Main,Kokona,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.17,0:02:04.47,Main,Shizuka,0,0,0,,Did they say anything about you, Kokona?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.72,0:02:06.05,Main,Kokona,0,0,0,,Just a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.92,0:02:10.83,Main,Shizuka,0,0,0,,"A performance of note\Nwas Kokona Otori as Aladdin."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.83,0:02:17.36,Main,Shizuka,0,0,0,,"Her Aladdin was overflowing with humanity,\N and she captivated the audience."
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.62,0:02:22.49,Main,Shizuka,0,0,0,,That's amazing! This writer is famous \Nfor being a super-harsh critic!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.96,0:02:27.74,Main,Kokona,0,0,0,,This means our acting\Nreached the audience, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.77,0:02:33.04,Main,Shizuka,0,0,0,,Let's buy another copy.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.04,0:02:33.83,Main,Kokona,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.83,0:02:36.54,Main,Shizuka,0,0,0,,We need to send it to your parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.64,0:02:39.62,Main,Kokona,0,0,0,,Yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.36,0:02:44.80,Main,Panda,0,0,0,,When you think of summer...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.63,0:02:50.79,Main,Panda,0,0,0,,This is the stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.79,0:02:52.81,Main,Sasuga,0,0,0,,It's a summer tradition.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.81,0:02:56.06,Main,Panda,0,0,0,,So, how do you find things at SIRIUS lately?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.33,0:02:59.33,Main,Sasuga,0,0,0,,I think things are relaxing quite nicely.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.07,0:03:05.31,Main,Panda,0,0,0,,Koko-chan, Kathrin, and Niizumacchi all seem \Nto be affecting each other positively.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.31,0:03:06.81,Main,Panda,0,0,0,,They're in top form now.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.81,0:03:08.64,Main,Sasuga,0,0,0,,They sure are.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.68,0:03:16.25,Main,Panda,0,0,0,,You know, I think we might just make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.25,0:03:18.98,Main,Panda,0,0,0,,If we can keep this hype going,\Nwe might be able to get
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.55,0:03:21.42,Main,Panda,0,0,0,,SIRIUS back to how it used to be...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.15,0:03:26.32,Main,Panda,0,0,0,,Um, hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.32,0:03:27.13,Main,Sasuga,0,0,0,,Hmm?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.51,0:03:28.77,Main,Panda,0,0,0,,Keep it coming.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.66,0:03:36.14,Main,Hiiragi,0,0,0,,Today, we start rehearsal for our\Nannual special theatrical showcase.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.59,0:03:38.69,Main,Kokona,0,0,0,,Special theatrical showcase?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.69,0:03:44.53,Main,Panda,0,0,0,,Every year, SIRIUS puts on a performance\Nfor the grade school kids of Taito Ward.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.53,0:03:49.67,Main,Panda,0,0,0,,We're looking for interested children,\Nand the chosen are invited to our troupe.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.67,0:03:54.58,Main,Hiiragi,0,0,0,,The showcase is also for the\Npurpose of nurturing future Dai Stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.58,0:03:59.04,Main,Hiiragi,0,0,0,,Remain focused in order to put on\Na good show for your younger peers.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.04,0:04:00.16,Main,Panda,0,0,0,,Hiiragi-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.52,0:04:01.35,Main,Hiiragi,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.35,0:04:06.94,Main,Panda,0,0,0,,Um... Has the play already been decided?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.50,0:04:13.47,Main,Hiiragi,0,0,0,,It's {\i1}King Lear{\i0}, same as last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.22,0:04:19.25,Main,Panda,0,0,0,,I knew it...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.98,0:04:22.20,Main,Sasuga,0,0,0,,The boss is dead set on it...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.20,0:04:24.76,Main,Panda,0,0,0,,But doing {\i1}King Lear{\i0}\Nfor grade schoolers is, uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.76,0:04:28.39,Main,Hiiragi,0,0,0,,We don't have much time to rehearse, \Nso I chose the same play.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.39,0:04:29.77,Main,Hiiragi,0,0,0,,Any objections?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.15,0:04:32.52,Main,Kokona,0,0,0,,What's {\i1}King Lear{\i0} about?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.52,0:04:36.16,Main,Shizuka,0,0,0,,A king betrayed by his daughters\Nand exiled from his land
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.16,0:04:38.93,Main,Shizuka,0,0,0,,is taken by madness and slowly withers.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.93,0:04:41.36,Main,Shizuka,0,0,0,,It's a tragedy about human absurdity.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.11,0:04:48.06,Main,Hiiragi,0,0,0,,If you have something to say, then say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.06,0:04:51.31,Main,Kathrina,0,0,0,,Why are we doing {\i1}King Lear{\i0} for \Na bunch of grade school kids?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.48,0:04:53.30,Main - Italics,Terahara and Kamiyashiki,0,0,0,,She actually said it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.30,0:04:56.80,Main - Italics,Panda,0,0,0,,Excellent, Kathrin! You tell her!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.01,0:04:59.90,Main,Kathrina,0,0,0,,{\i1}King Lear{\i0} is one of Shakespeare's \Nfour great tragedies,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.90,0:05:02.64,Main,Kathrina,0,0,0,,but it's famous for being \None of the most difficult.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.64,0:05:05.00,Main,Kathrina,0,0,0,,Seems a bit much for children.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.00,0:05:07.87,Main,Hiiragi,0,0,0,,True, the play might be difficult,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.87,0:05:12.36,Main,Hiiragi,0,0,0,,but it's also important for kids to see the \Nclassics when they're impressionable.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.36,0:05:13.90,Main,Kathrina,0,0,0,,Will they even understand it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.18,0:05:16.96,Main,Hiiragi,0,0,0,,It's our job to make sure they do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.97,0:05:20.72,Main - Italics,Panda,0,0,0,,It's no use...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.72,0:05:24.30,Main - Italics,Panda,0,0,0,,At this rate,\Nthe same tragedy will befall us!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.96,0:05:28.90,Flashback,Boy,0,0,0,,I'm scared!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.90,0:05:30.70,Flashback,Girl,0,0,0,,Take me home!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.70,0:05:31.98,Flashback,Kids,0,0,0,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.73,0:05:35.47,Flashback,Kids,0,0,0,,I wanna go home!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.30,0:05:42.57,Main - Italics,Terahara,0,0,0,,What should we do?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.57,0:05:44.26,Main - Italics,Kamiyashiki,0,0,0,,There has to be something we can do!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.26,0:05:45.43,Main - Italics,Sasuga,0,0,0,,Panda...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.55,0:05:48.75,Main,Hiiragi,0,0,0,,When I was in grade school,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.75,0:05:54.58,Main,Hiiragi,0,0,0,,I saw {\i1}King Lear{\i0} at the National Theatre\N in London and was deeply moved!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.58,0:05:57.99,Main,Panda,0,0,0,,For sure! {\i1}King Lear{\i0} is an absolute classic!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.99,0:06:00.31,Main,Panda,0,0,0,,I'm sure many would be moved by it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.31,0:06:04.19,Main,Panda,0,0,0,,But last year, the kids got scared\Nand cried in the middle of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.19,0:06:05.01,Main,Girls,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah, yeah!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.22,0:06:07.42,Main,Hiiragi,0,0,0,,Well, there isn't anything we can do—
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.81,0:06:08.53,Overlap,Panda,0,0,0,,Of course there is!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.53,0:06:13.23,Main,Panda,0,0,0,,The point of the showcase\Nis to nurture future Dai Stars.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.23,0:06:16.51,Main,Panda,0,0,0,,As Kathrin said, {\i1}King Lear{\i0} is a bit \Nmuch for grade schoolers.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.51,0:06:20.04,Main,Panda,0,0,0,,So what we need to do is choose a play
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.04,0:06:24.03,Main,Panda,0,0,0,,that can move {\i1}everyone{\i0} and\Nget them to fall in love with theater!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.33,0:06:25.95,Main,Sasuga,0,0,0,,I agree with Panda.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.95,0:06:27.62,Main,Terahara and Kamiyashiki,0,0,0,,We do too!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.60,0:06:39.17,Main,Hiiragi,0,0,0,,I guess you have a point.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.79,0:06:47.67,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,{\fad(190,1)\pos(324.667,42)\fnTimes New Roman\b1\shad0\c&H627A89&\3c&HF6F8F8&}Victory!!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.36,0:06:47.66,Main,Kathrin,0,0,0,,What in the world happened last year?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.92,0:06:52.85,Main,Kudo,0,0,0,,This is going to be a test performance, \Nso why don't we leave it to the girls?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.97,0:06:57.93,Main,Hiiragi,0,0,0,,All right, let's discuss what play to put on.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.24,0:07:02.07,Main,Kathrina,0,0,0,,How about one like {\i1}The Little \NMermaid {\i0}that's based on a fairytale?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.07,0:07:06.43,Main,Panda,0,0,0,,That's a great idea. SIRIUS \Nhas quite a few in its repetoire.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.65,0:07:10.91,Main,Kokona,0,0,0,,If we want them to get a real taste of \Ntheater, maybe it {\i1}should{\i0} be Shakespeare?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.91,0:07:14.94,Main,Shizuka,0,0,0,,I think a comedy would be easier\Nfor a child to understand than a tragedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.94,0:07:17.76,Main,Kathrina,0,0,0,,Well, if it's a Shakespearean comedy we want...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.76,0:07:22.38,Main,Sasuga,0,0,0,,{\i1}Twelfth Night{\i0}, {\i1}As You Like It{\i0}, \N or {\i1}Much Ado About Nothing{\i0}, probably?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.38,0:07:27.45,Main,Panda,0,0,0,,Hmm... We should probably go with \Nsomething a little more mainstream.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.76,0:07:31.67,Main,Niizuma,0,0,0,,This is rather orthodox,\Nbut how about {\i1}Romeo and Juliet{\i0}?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.25,0:07:36.88,Main,Niizuma,0,0,0,,{\i1}Romeo and Juliet{\i0} is usually \Nconsidered a tragedy,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.88,0:07:39.10,Main,Niizuma,0,0,0,,but it also has romantic comedy aspects.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.49,0:07:44.35,Main,Niizuma,0,0,0,,The story is also very moving and easy to \Nfollow, so I think they might enjoy it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.85,0:07:47.61,Main,Kathrina,0,0,0,,I think that's fine.\NI'm sure they all know it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.84,0:07:50.02,Main,Kokona,0,0,0,,It {\i1}is{\i0} pretty famous.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.31,0:07:51.88,Main,Hiiragi,0,0,0,,Sounds like we have our play.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.88,0:07:55.63,Main,Hiiragi,0,0,0,,We'll be doing {\i1}Romeo and Juliet{\i0} \Nfor the special theatrical showcase.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.96,0:07:59.36,Main,Kokona,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.03,0:08:02.67,Main,Kokona,0,0,0,,You're not going to be in it, Yae-chan?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.04,0:08:02.67,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,{\an7\fnArial\fs14\i1\c&H313331&\3c&HDADCDC&\shad0\bord3}Romeo and Juliet{\i0} Roles\N Romeo: Sasuga\N Juliet: Panda\N Benvolio: Kokona\NCount Paris: Terahara\N Friar Laurence: Kathrina\NTybalt: Kamiyashiki
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.67,0:08:08.17,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,{\fad(350,1)\an8\fnArial\b1\shad0\bord4\c&H43F7F2&\3c&H060741&}Grade Schooler
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.00,0:08:08.17,Main,Niizuma,0,0,0,,Well, I'm in grade school too. I'll be in \Nthe audience cheering you all on this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.42,0:08:15.93,Signs,Sign,0,0,0,,{\an8\fnArial\fs20\shad0\c&H1C1D1C&\3c&HE6E9E6&\t(1980,3650,\3c&H8E8C8A&)}Count Paris: Terahara\NFriar Laurence: Kathrina\NTybalt: Kamiyashiki
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.42,0:08:14.93,Main,Kathrina,0,0,0,,I'm playing another support role...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.87,0:08:20.20,Main,Sasuga,0,0,0,,Are you okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.26,0:08:23.15,Main,Panda,0,0,0,,Oh, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.70,0:08:27.55,Main,Panda,0,0,0,,{\i1}Romeo and Juliet{\i0} brings back\Na lot of memories for me,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.55,0:08:32.05,Main,Panda,0,0,0,,so playing in it gives me\Na lot to think about.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.32,0:08:42.78,Main,Kokona,0,0,0,,Sasuga-chan! I'll be Romeo's friend Benvolio.\N I look forward to acting alongside you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.20,0:08:44.48,Main,Sasuga,0,0,0,,Same.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.48,0:08:47.08,Main,Shizuka,0,0,0,,I can't wait to see you two star in this play.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.08,0:08:50.20,Main,Niizuma,0,0,0,,I'm excited to learn from your performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.20,0:08:53.10,Main,Panda,0,0,0,,No way! You saying that is...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.38,0:08:57.90,Main,Hiiragi,0,0,0,,Make sure you two show your \Nyounger peers what you've got.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.13,0:08:59.59,Main,Panda,0,0,0,,Hiiragi-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.13,0:08:59.59,Overlap,Sasuga,0,0,0,,Boss...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.59,0:09:03.24,Main,Hiiragi,0,0,0,,I'm sure that girl will \Nbe back again this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.59,0:09:06.12,Main,Panda,0,0,0,,Ah...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.88,0:09:10.65,Main,Panda,0,0,0,,So {\i1}she's{\i0} coming back.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.18,0:09:16.29,Main,Kudo,0,0,0,,The ward office said that she entered herself \Nin the ticket raffle hundreds of times.
